.TH "HPC\-COMPOSE\-PLAN" "1" "" "hpc\-compose 0.1.34" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
hpc\-compose\-plan \- Validate and preview a static execution plan
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
hpc\-compose plan [OPTIONS]
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
Run the safe static authoring path: validate the compose file, build the normalized runtime plan, and optionally print the generated launcher script without touching Slurm, preparing images, or writing script files.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB-f\fR, \fB--file\fR \fIFILE\fR
Compose specification file to read; if omitted, use the active context compose file or fall back to compose.yaml.
.TP
\fB--strict\-env\fR
Fail when ${VAR:\-default} or ${VAR\-default} fallbacks are used because VAR is missing.
.TP
\fB--verbose\fR
Include resolved environment values and final mount mappings.
.TP
\fB--tree\fR
Show services as a dependency tree.
.TP
\fB--show\-script\fR
Print the rendered launcher script to stdout after the plan.
.TP
\fB--format\fR \fIFORMAT\fR
Output format. Possible values: text, json.
.TP
\fB--color\fR \fIWHEN\fR
Controls colored output. Default: auto. Possible values: auto, always, never.
.TP
\fB--quiet\fR
Suppress progress indicators and non\-essential labels.
.TP
\fB--profile\fR \fINAME\fR
Profile name to load from .hpc\-compose/settings.toml.
.TP
\fB--settings\-file\fR \fIPATH\fR
Explicit settings file path; defaults to upward search for .hpc\-compose/settings.toml.
.TP
\fB-h\fR, \fB--help\fR
Print help (see a summary with '\-h').
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
hpc\-compose plan \-f compose.yaml
hpc\-compose plan \-\-verbose \-f compose.yaml
hpc\-compose plan \-\-show\-script \-f compose.yaml
hpc\-compose plan \-f compose.yaml \-\-format json
.fi
